cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.IT. 

The paper concerns the hardness of approximation for a variant of Label Cover, which is a classic problem in computational complexity theory. This suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and connectivity problems, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as possible sub-categories. The use of reductions and approximation algorithms suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as additional possibilities.
